      • authenticate

        public boolean authenticate(int blockIndex,
                   int keyType,
                   byte[] key,
                   byte[] uid)
                     throws SDKException
        To authenticate one block of mifare classic card.
        Parameters:
        blockIndex - the block no be authenticated, 0~63 for S50, and 0~255 for S70.
        keyType - the key type for authenticated,refer to KEY_TYPE_A or KEY_TYPE_B
        key - the key information, 6bytes long.
        uid - the uid information of mifare classic card.the last 4 bytes which return from getUID()
        Returns:
        returns true if authenticated success else failure.
        Throws:
        SDKException

      • readBlock

        public byte[] readBlock(int blockIndex)
                 throws SDKException
        To read the block data-read one block from mifare classic card by index.
        Parameters:
        blockIndex - the index of block no be read out, 0~63 for S50, and 0~255 for S70.
        Returns:
        retruns the block data read from mifare classic, 16bytes long if success else throws exception.
        Throws:
        SDKException
